==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moot-hill
<hw>Moot"-hill`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(O. Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>A hill of meeting or council; an elevated place in the
open air where public assemblies or courts were held by the Saxons; --
called, in Scotland, <altname>mute-hill</altname>.</def> <rj><au>J. R.
Green.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mootman</ent>⟦br⟧
